      <p>
        I graduated from my high school in 2023, and I started my university
        studies at the University of Auckland. I was accepted into the Computer
        Science and IT Management double major program.
      </p>
      <p>
        In January 2024, I was asked to be a teacher aide for the Japanese
        international students at my high school for a month, and I helped them
        settle into school and resolve any issues, whether school- or
        homestay-related. I also made sure they were not being left behind in
        class.
      </p>
      <p>
        In March 2024, I joined the Yamada UI maintainer team and have been
        contributing since. I learned a lot from the Yamada UI team and continue
        to learn more.
      </p>
      <p>
        In July 2024, I was hired by YAGO as a teacher for <a
          href="https://kids.classmall.jp/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">classmall Kids</a
        >, which teaches programming to Japanese children on Minecraft
        Education.
      </p>
      <p>
        In October 2024, I started contributing to <a
          href="https://zen-browser.app/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">Zen Browser</a
        >'s website and joined their contribution team in November.
      </p>
      <p>
        In April 2025, I joined the Web Development and Consulting Club at the
        University of Auckland. I've developed a website for <a
          href="https://uoabadminton.co.nz"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">University of Auckland Badminton Club</a
        > with an awesome team throughout the year.
      </p>
      <p>
        In November 2025, I joined <a
          href="https://hazumi.co.jp"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">Hazumi Inc.</a
        > as a software engineer.
      </p>
